Open Textbook Workshop Code

Introduction - About this Tutorial (1/15)
<p><span style="font-size:14px;">This tutorial is an an&nbsp;asynchronous online workshop about Open Educational Resources</span></p>

<p><span style="font-size:14px;">In this presentation you will...</span></p>

<ul>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Learn about Open Educational Resources and Creative Commons</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Identify common issues in the economics of higher education and the textbook industry</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Interpret the publishing model and how Creative Commons transforms it to give more rights and permissions back to the creator</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Recognize your rights as a creator under Creative Commons, Open Education, and Open Pedagogy</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Analyze&nbsp;the efficacy of Open Educational Resources through literature reviews</span></li>
	<li><span style="font-size:14px;">Locate and access Open Educational Resources for your own courses</span></li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><span style="font-size:14px;"></span></strong></p>

